The paper deals with the problem of finding square roots of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves determining if a given graph is the square of some other graph, which is related to graph theory (cs.CG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the characterization and recognition of graphs with certain properties, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT) and algorithms/data structures (cs.DS).
